---
/**
 * streaming-event-driven · exactly-once-kafka-deep-dive · Figure 3 — the partition
 * log, the Last Stable Offset, and the two isolation levels (Level 3).
 *
 * Verbatim from the source HTML (figure + svg + figcaption). This figure has no
 * marker refs, but is kept as a component for the same SVG-in-MDX reason.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 600 168"
        role="img"
        aria-label="A partition log with committed records, then aborted records, then an open transaction. read_committed stops at the Last Stable Offset before the open transaction and filters aborted records; read_uncommitted returns everything."
    >
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <text
                x="300"
                y="18"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11.5"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#111110">one partition's log →</text
            >
            <!-- committed run -->
            <g>
                <rect x="14" y="34" width="44" height="34" rx="5" fill="#eef5ee" stroke="#2f5d3a"
                ></rect>
                <rect x="62" y="34" width="44" height="34" rx="5" fill="#eef5ee" stroke="#2f5d3a"
                ></rect>
                <rect x="110" y="34" width="44" height="34" rx="5" fill="#eef5ee" stroke="#2f5d3a"
                ></rect>
                <text x="84" y="84" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#2f5d3a"
                    >committed</text
                >
            </g>
            <!-- aborted -->
            <g>
                <rect x="166" y="34" width="44" height="34" rx="5" fill="#f7ecea" stroke="#9a2417"
                ></rect>
                <rect x="214" y="34" width="44" height="34" rx="5" fill="#f7ecea" stroke="#9a2417"
                ></rect>
                <text x="210" y="84" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#9a2417"
                    >aborted (filtered)</text
                >
            </g>
            <!-- open txn -->
            <g>
                <rect
                    x="300"
                    y="34"
                    width="44"
                    height="34"
                    rx="5"
                    fill="#fff"
                    stroke="#6b675f"
                    stroke-dasharray="3 2"></rect>
                <rect
                    x="348"
                    y="34"
                    width="44"
                    height="34"
                    rx="5"
                    fill="#fff"
                    stroke="#6b675f"
                    stroke-dasharray="3 2"></rect>
                <text x="346" y="84" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#6b675f"
                    >open txn (undecided)</text
                >
            </g>
            <!-- LSO marker -->
            <line x1="288" y1="26" x2="288" y2="100" stroke="#7a1f12" stroke-width="1.5"></line>
            <text
                x="288"
                y="114"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#7a1f12">LSO</text
            >
            <text x="288" y="127" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >first open txn</text
            >
            <!-- readers -->
            <rect x="40" y="134" width="220" height="28" rx="14" fill="#eef5ee" stroke="#2f5d3a"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="150"
                y="152"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="9.5"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#2f5d3a">read_committed → committed only, stops at LSO</text
            >
            <rect x="320" y="134" width="260" height="28" rx="14" fill="#f7ecea" stroke="#9a2417"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="450"
                y="152"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="9.5"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#9a2417">read_uncommitted → everything: committed + aborted + in-flight</text
            >
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        The LSO is the offset just before the first still-open transaction;
        <code>read_committed</code> never reads past it, and filters aborted records via the broker's
        markers.
    </figcaption>
</figure>
